  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Dinner tonight turned into a much bigger family affair than usual, since my aunt showed up with a major announcement.",
      "zh": "今晚的晚餐變成了一場比平常盛大很多的家族聚會，因為我姑姑帶著一個重大消息出現。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She is getting married, and the room got so loud with excitement that even Perry started barking, unsure of what to think.",
      "zh": "她要結婚了，房間頓時因為興奮變得超吵，連 Perry 都跟著吠了起來，搞不清楚該有什麼反應。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Her future husband is a tall, quiet man who works in media, and he shook everyone's hand politely upon his arrival.",
      "zh": "她未來的先生是個又高又安靜的男人，在媒體業工作，一到場就很有禮貌地跟每個人握手。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia immediately asked about the wedding date, the guest list, and, with real concern, whether there would be enough space for everyone.",
      "zh": "Sophia 馬上問了婚禮日期、賓客名單，還很認真地問位子夠不夠所有人坐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My uncle joked that the whole family has a shared trait: none of us can discuss anything without turning it into a production.",
      "zh": "我叔叔開玩笑說我們全家有個共同的特質：什麼事都能被我們搞得跟一場大製作一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, though absent-minded about most adult topics, understood one important detail immediately: weddings usually have cake.",
      "zh": "雖然 William 對大部分大人的話題都心不在焉，但他馬上懂了一個重要的細節：婚禮通常都有蛋糕。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My aunt said the wedding would be a small, secondary celebration compared to the main ceremony, held later at her fiancé's family home up north.",
      "zh": "我姑姑說這次算是比較小的、次要的慶祝，主要的儀式之後會在她未婚夫家北部的老家舉行。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad poured a small glass of wine for the adults and said, with a proud expression, that this was cause enough for a proper toast.",
      "zh": "爸爸幫大人們各倒了一小杯酒，帶著驕傲的表情說，這已經值得好好敬一杯了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"To family, old and new,\" he said, and everyone raised their glass, including William, who raised a cup of plain water instead.",
      "zh": "「敬家人，不管是老是新，」他說，大家都舉起了杯子，包括 William，只是他舉的是一杯白開水。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My aunt showed us a recent photo of the venue, a lovely place with a stone path and flowers along both sides.",
      "zh": "我姑姑給我們看了場地最近拍的照片，一個很美的地方，石頭小路兩旁都種著花。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, who happened to be at our house that evening, immediately asked if she could be some kind of flower girl for the ceremony.",
      "zh": "剛好那天晚上在我家的 Bernice，馬上問她能不能當個什麼花童之類的角色。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My aunt laughed and said, in all fairness, she would have to check with the rest of the wedding party first before deciding.",
      "zh": "我姑姑笑著說，說句公道話，她得先跟婚禮團隊其他人商量一下才能決定。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia mentioned an old family tradition regarding weddings: the bride's grandmother must personally choose the dessert selection.",
      "zh": "Sophia 提到一個跟婚禮有關的老家族傳統：新娘的祖母必須親自挑選甜點的選項。"
    },
    {
      "en": "As the head of our family in that regard, she declared she would allow no fewer than three types of cake at the reception.",
      "zh": "身為我們家在這方面的話事人，她宣布婚宴上至少要有三種蛋糕，一種都不能少。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of the night, everyone was tired but glad, and the whole dinner table felt closer than it had in a long time.",
      "zh": "晚上結束時，大家都累了但很開心，整張餐桌感覺比很久以來都更親密。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William fell asleep on the couch before dessert even arrived, still holding his empty water cup like a tiny, exhausted toast-giver.",
      "zh": "William 甜點都還沒上桌就在沙發上睡著了，手裡還握著他空空的水杯，像個累壞了的迷你敬酒人。"
    }
  ],
